# Option A — use the Flutter app .env at repo root (recommended):
#   SUPABASE_URL=https://xxxx.supabase.co
#   SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJ... or sb_publishable_...
#
# Option B — override only for this portal:
#   VITE_SUPABASE_URL=...
#   VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=...
#
# Vercel / CI: add the same keys in the dashboard (Environment Variables). No .env file is required there.
#
# Optional Storage browser:
#   VITE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your-bucket-name
#
# Dev-only (opt-in): proxy Supabase via Vite so the browser only talks to localhost (helps if extensions block *.supabase.co).
# Leave unset for normal direct HTTPS to Supabase. Enable with:
#   VITE_SUPABASE_DEV_PROXY=true
#
# Merged .env files (incl. this file) override shell env for Supabase URL/keys — avoids placeholder URLs in the terminal.
#
# Student / attendance photos (Backblaze B2):
#   Production uses the same Supabase Edge Function as the Flutter app: `b2-storage-proxy` (action `download_auth`).
#   Local dev can also sign via Vite when B2B_* are in ../MSCE 2/.env or ../MSCE/.env.
#   Optional override: VITE_B2_SIGN_API=https://your-host/api/b2-sign-photo
